// Copilot: Build a complete "Risk Profile & Suggested Asset Allocation" flow in React with TailwindCSS
// Requirements:
//
// Project Structure
//  - src/pages/RiskProfileIntro.jsx      → Introduction + Start button
//  - src/pages/RiskProfileQuestions.jsx  → Multi-step questionnaire
//  - src/pages/RiskProfileResult.jsx     → Allocation result (chart + table + save button)
//  - src/components/QuestionCard.jsx     → Reusable component for displaying a single question with choices
//  - src/utils/allocationLogic.js        → Helper function generateAllocation(answers)
//  - src/api/userApi.js                  → Stubbed saveRiskProfile API (mock POST)
//
// 1. RiskProfileIntro.jsx
// - Simple page explaining the purpose of risk profiling
// - Clean Tailwind design with centered content
// - "Start Questionnaire" button → navigates to /risk-questions
//
// 2. RiskProfileQuestions.jsx
// - Step-by-step multi-question flow (7 questions as defined below)
// - Show progress indicator (Step X of 7)
// - Use <QuestionCard /> for each question
// - Navigation: "Back" + "Next"
// - Save answers in state { q1, q2, q3, ... }
// - On final step → call generateAllocation(answers) and redirect to /risk-result
//
// Questions:
//   a) Investment Time Horizon (Short <3 yrs, Medium 3–7 yrs, Long >7 yrs)
//   b) Risk Appetite (Low, Moderate, High)
//   c) Income vs Expenses (Surplus, Break-even, Deficit)
//   d) Investment Knowledge (Beginner, Intermediate, Advanced)
//   e) Comfort with Market Volatility (Low, Medium, High)
//   f) Preferred Assets (Stocks, Mutual Funds, Gold, Real Estate, Debt)
//   g) Liquidity Preference (High, Medium, Low)
//
// 3. RiskProfileResult.jsx
// - Displays results after allocation
// - Show Donut Chart (react-chartjs-2 or recharts)
// - Show summary table/cards with allocation percentages
// - Button: "Save My Profile"
// - On click → calls saveRiskProfile(userId, answers, allocation)
//
// 4. QuestionCard.jsx
// - Props: { questionText, options, selected, onChange }
// - Renders question with Tailwind cards as multiple choice
//
// 5. allocationLogic.js
// - export function generateAllocation(answers) {}
// - Implements allocation logic:
//   - Conservative → Debt + Gold heavy, low equity
//   - Moderate → Balanced mix
//   - Aggressive → Equity heavy
//   - Always sum to 100%
//   - If asset not selected → assign 0%
// - Example output: { equityMF: 40, stocks: 20, debt: 25, gold: 10, realEstate: 0, liquid: 5 }
//
// 6. userApi.js
// - export async function saveRiskProfile(userId, answers, allocation) {}
// - Stub POST request (mock URL for now)
// - Assume userId from Cognito, but for now use "test-user"
//
// UX Notes
// - Use Tailwind for responsive, mobile-first clean UI
// - Smooth transitions between steps
// - Keep questionnaire minimal and user-friendly
//
// Deliverables
// - All pages + components + utils + API stub as listed above
// - Full navigation flow: Intro → Questions → Result